  "prompt": "What are the symptoms of anxiety?",
  "response": "Anxiety can manifest in various ways, both physically and psychologically. Common symptoms of anxiety include:\n\n1. **Psychological Symptoms:**\n   - Excessive worry or fear\n   - Feeling restless or on edge\n   - Difficulty concentrating or having a blank mind\n   - Irritability\n   - A sense of impending doom or danger\n\n2. **Physical Symptoms:**\n   - Increased heart rate or palpitations\n   - Shortness of breath or rapid breathing\n   - Sweating\n   - Trembling or shaking\n   - Fatigue or weakness\n   - Headaches\n   - Muscle tension or aches\n   - Stomach upset or nausea\n   - Difficulty sleeping (insomnia)\n\n3. **Behavioral Symptoms:**\n   - Avoidance of situations that cause anxiety\n   - Compulsive behaviors or rituals to reduce anxiety (common in OCD)\n   - Restlessness or inability to sit still\n\nIt's important to note that anxiety can vary in severity and may present differently in different individuals. If you or someone you know is experiencing persistent anxiety that interferes with daily life, it may be beneficial to seek professional help from a mental health provider.",
